    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-02-05T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-02-05T18:00:00-05:00" n="248"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d248">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94 Commission/66: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Shanghai (<persName corresp="#p_CES1" type="to"
                            >Cunningham</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-02-05T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 5, 1932—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Department assumes that the Minister has instructed you that you should
                        cooperate with the members of the Shanghai Commission in studying and
                        reporting upon the facts and causes of the incidents at Shanghai.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>You should not sign the report but should address letter to Chairman of
                        Commission, signing as American Consul General, either stating that you
                        concur in the Commission’s report or indicating any particulars <pb
                            facs="0332" n="228" xml:id="pg_228"/> in which you do not concur in the
                        report. Telegraph action taken.<note n="63" xml:id="d248fn63">See telegram
                            No. 17, February 8, 6 p.m., from the Consul General at Shanghai, <ref
                                target="#pg_254">p. 254</ref>.</note>
                    </item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>Repeat to Nanking.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SHL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
